{
  "texts": [
    "Out of the 23 successful adversarial attacks, they are categorized as follows: 4 attacks (17.39%) were related to misconceptions and biases in AI responses, 7 attacks (30.43%) were driven by pressing for more detailed explanations, 6 attacks (26.09%) fell under refinement with limitations, and 6 attacks (26.09%) involved making things up.",
    "The topic \"Acids and Bases\" had the highest number of adversarial prompts, with 17 cases, of which 6 were successful (35.29%) and 11 failed (64.71%).",
    "In \"Atomic Structure\", both adversarial attacks failed, resulting in a 100% failure rate.",
    "\"Chemical Bonds\" had only one adversarial prompt, which succeeded.",
    "In contrast, \"Chemical Reactions\" saw a high success rate, with 8 out of 9 adversarial attacks (88.89%) succeeding."
  ]
}